  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 11th level, you gain the ability to create an orb of light that erupts into a devastating explosion. As an action, you magically create an orb and hurl it at a point you choose within 150 feet, where it erupts into a sphere of radiant light for a brief but deadly instant.</p>\n<p>Each creature in that 20-foot-radius sphere must succeed on a <strong>Constitution saving throw</strong> or take <strong>2d6 radiant damage</strong>. A creature doesn't need to make the save if the creature is behind total cover that is opaque.</p>\n<p>You can increase the sphere's damage by spending @Compendium[5e-complete.5e-class-features.imsZ2GYUPlwCQqqy]{ki points}. Each point you spend, <strong>up to a maximum of 3</strong>, increases the damage by [[/r 2d6]].</p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><em>Note: When adding bonus damage, use the roll button above and deduct the appropriate number of ki points spent manually.</em></p>\n</section>",
